Class Transition

java.lang.Object
io.github.leobeaumont.Transition
public class Transition extends Object
Represents a transition in a Petri net, responsible for moving tokens from input places to output places via edges.

  • Method Details

    • isDrawable

      public boolean isDrawable()
      Determines whether this transition can be drawn (activated).

      A transition can be drawn if all its incoming edges are activable.

      Returns:
      true if the transition can be drawn; false otherwise

    • draw

      public void draw()
      Draws (activates) the transition.

      This method calls Edge.activate() on all connected incoming and outgoing edges.
